quran[6]{c,v,t,f}:
  6,109,"And they swear by Allāh their strongest oaths that if a sign came to them, they would surely believe in it. Say, "
  6,110,"And We will turn away their hearts and their eyes just as they refused to believe in it [i.e., the revelation] the first time. And We will leave them in their transgression, wandering blindly."
  6,111,"And even if We had sent down to them the angels [with the message] and the dead spoke to them [of it] and We gathered together every [created] thing in front of them, they would not believe unless Allāh should will. But most of them, [of that], are ignorant."
  7,19,"And "
  7,20,"But Satan whispered to them to make apparent to them that which was concealed from them of their private parts. He said, "
  7,21,"And he swore [by Allāh] to them, "